title: As Ukraine flies through artillery rounds, U.S. races to keep up
description: Washington has sent Kyiv millions of munitions, but restocking the U.S. arsenal and building new production lines is a multi-billion-dollar problem.

title: Egypt’s president pardons prominent activist Ahmed Douma
description: Douma led protests during Egypt’s 2011 revolution but has since spent nearly a decade behind bars.

title: British Columbia declares state of emergency amid ‘devastating’ wildfires
description: “We are facing the worst wildfire season in our province’s history,” British Columbia’s premier warned, as flames threatened Kelowna and West Kelowna.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Ukraine, Romania work on grain transit route after Russia deal collapse
description: The agreement follows Russia’s departure from the U.N.-backed grain deal, which had allowed for the safe wartime transport of foodstuffs over the Black Sea.

title: Russian court dissolves Sakharov Center, a prominent human rights group
description: The organization, named after Nobel Peace laureate and Soviet dissident Andrei Sakharov, ran a museum and cultural space in Moscow.

title: As Syria burns, and its economy collapses, firefighters appeal for support
description: The fires sweeping across northwestern Syria this summer have compounded an already dire situation in a region still divided by conflict and isolated from the world.
